---
const samples = "https://github.com/veilensapp/veilens/tree/main/examples/vault";
const tap = "brew install veilensapp/tap/veilens";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>Ask your documents — veilens walkthrough</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A start-to-finish walkthrough: index your own bank statements and ask questions about them — answered entirely on your Mac, with the data never leaving the machine."
    />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Ask your own documents — veilens" />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="Index your bank statements and ask questions about them, answered locally. A start-to-finish walkthrough."
    />
    <meta property="og:type" content="article" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://veilens.app/walkthrough" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <header class="top">
        <a class="back" href="/">← veilens</a>
        <a class="src" href="https://github.com/veilensapp/veilens">veilens ↗</a>
      </header>

      <section class="intro">
        <span class="kicker">walkthrough · experimental</span>
        <h1>Summarize and query your own bank statements</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          A start-to-finish example of the <a href="https://github.com/veilensapp/veilens">veilens</a>
          vault: drop a folder of PDFs on your Mac, index them, and ask
          open-ended questions — <strong>"how much did I spend on travel last
          year?", "when does my insurance renew?"</strong> — answered by a
          frontier model that <strong>writes code but never sees your data</strong>.
          Everything runs on Apple Silicon; the documents and the answers stay on
          the machine.
        </p>
        <p class="experimental">
          ⚠︎ <strong>Experimental.</strong> This is an early research flow — the
          pieces are moving and it isn't ready to trust with data that truly
          matters yet.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ── 1 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="step">
        <div class="num">1</div>
        <div class="body">
          <h2>Gather your documents</h2>
          <p>
            Export your statements from your bank or insurer's website as PDF and
            drop them in a folder — say <code>~/vault</code>. Bank exports are
            <em>digital</em> PDFs (a real text layer), which is exactly what the
            extractor reads. CSVs and Markdown notes work too. Nothing is uploaded
            anywhere; this folder just sits on your disk.
          </p>
          <p class="note">
            No data of your own to test with? Grab the
            <a href={samples}>sample vault</a> — a few fictional statements, an
            insurance policy, and a vehicle registration:
          </p>
          <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/veilensapp/veilens
cp veilens/examples/vault/*.pdf ~/vault</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── 2 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="step">
        <div class="num">2</div>
        <div class="body">
          <h2>Install veilens</h2>
          <p>
            Install the <strong><code>veilens</code> CLI</strong> via Homebrew:
          </p>
          <pre><code>{tap}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── 3 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="step">
        <div class="num">3</div>
        <div class="body">
          <h2>Set up the vault</h2>
          <p>
            One command installs the whole stack — the inference server (a
            <strong>chat model</strong> that reads your documents and an
            <strong>embedding model</strong> for search, both served from one
            port), the <a href="/headgate">headgate</a> harness, and the veilens vault —
            reusing anything already installed:
          </p>
          <pre><code>veilens install</code></pre>
          <p class="note">
            veilens bundles everything it needs — the
            <a href="https://millrace.app/server">millrace inference server</a>,
            the headgate harness, and the local vault site — installing each only
            if it isn't already there.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── 4 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="step">
        <div class="num">4</div>
        <div class="body">
          <h2>Index your vault</h2>
          <p>
            Point veilens at your folder. It chunks each file, embeds the chunks
            locally, and stores the vectors in an on-device
            <a href="https://github.com/millrace/lancedb.mojo">LanceDB</a> index —
            only you ever see the contents:
          </p>
          <pre><code>veilens index ~/vault</code></pre>
          <p class="note">
            veilens's <strong>manifest</strong> is the only thing the frontier
            model is ever shown — aliases like <code>file_0 [pdf]</code> and
            <code>col_2</code>, never names, values, or paths.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── 5 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="step">
        <div class="num">5</div>
        <div class="body">
          <h2>Ask</h2>
          <p>
            Open the vault chat — it brings the server up, launches the chat UI,
            and points your browser at it. Type a question and the frontier model
            writes a small program that searches your vault and reads the real
            text with the on-device model; the answer is computed locally.
          </p>
          <pre><code>veilens start       <span class="c"># opens http://localhost:10000</span></code></pre>
          <p>Prefer the terminal? A one-shot:</p>
          <pre><code>veilens ask "When does my car insurance renew?"</code></pre>
          <pre class="out"><code>Your car insurance renews on 2026-09-15.</code></pre>
          <p class="note">Done for the day? <code>veilens stop</code> shuts the
          whole stack back down.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ── why it's private ──────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section class="prose">
        <h2>Why this is private</h2>
        <p>
          The powerful model is treated as an <strong>untrusted code generator,
          not a data processor</strong>. It sees the <em>shape</em> of your vault
          (the aliased manifest) and writes code; the code runs locally, in a
          network-denied sandbox that can reach only <code>127.0.0.1</code>. The
          on-device model is the only thing that reads real content, and the
          answer is printed on your machine. Your statements never leave the Mac,
          and never reach the frontier model.
        </p>
      </section>

      <footer>
        <span>© veilens</span>
        <span class="dot">·</span>
        <a href="https://github.com/veilensapp/veilens">veilens</a>
        <span class="dot">·</span>
        <a href="/headgate">how the harness works →</a>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

<style is:global>
  :root {
    --bg-top: #284a5c;
    --bg-bot: #122632;
    --ink: #eaf1f6;
    --muted: #9fb4c2;
    --accent: #ff7a1c;
    --accent-lite: #ffb05c;
    --line: rgba(159, 180, 194, 0.18);
    --card: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html { color-scheme: dark; }

  body {
    margin: 0;
    min-height: 100vh;
    color: var(--ink);
    background:
      radial-gradient(1200px 600px at 50% -10%, rgba(255, 122, 28, 0.10), transparent 60%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-top), var(--bg-bot));
    background-attachment: fixed;
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Inter, Roboto,
      Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  a { color: var(--accent-lite); text-decoration: none; }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  main {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem) 1.5rem 3rem;
  }

  .top { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .back, .src { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .back:hover, .src:hover { color: var(--accent-lite); }

  .kicker {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent-lite);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #ffffff, #cedae6);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    color: transparent;
  }

  .lede { margin: 1.2rem 0 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .lede strong, .step strong, .prose strong { color: var(--ink); }

  .experimental {
    margin: 1.4rem 0 0;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 122, 28, 0.35);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: rgba(255, 122, 28, 0.07);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .experimental strong { color: var(--accent-lite); }

  /* ── numbered steps ─────────────────────────────────────── */
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.8rem);
  }
  .num {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    width: 2.1rem;
    height: 2.1rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a1207;
    background: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
  }
  .body { min-width: 0; flex: 1; }
  .body h2 { font-size: 1.35rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .body p { color: var(--muted); margin: 0.5rem 0; }
  .note { font-size: 0.92rem; }

  pre {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0.9rem 1.05rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0.7rem 0;
  }
  pre.out {
    background: rgba(255, 122, 28, 0.06);
    border-color: rgba(255, 122, 28, 0.3);
  }
  code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.92em;
  }
  p code, li code, .note code {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 0.05rem 0.35rem;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  pre code { background: none; border: 0; padding: 0; color: var(--ink); }
  pre.out code { color: var(--accent-lite); }
  pre .c { color: var(--muted); }

  .prose { margin-top: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.5rem); }
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .prose p { color: var(--muted); }

  footer {
    margin-top: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem);
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  footer a { color: var(--muted); }
  footer a:hover { color: var(--accent-lite); }
  .dot { margin: 0 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5; }
</style>
